&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="how-to-redirect-standard-error-in-bash">How to redirect standard error in bash&lt;/h2>
&lt;table>
 &lt;thead>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;th style="text-align: left">Command&lt;/th>
 &lt;th style="text-align: left">Description/Purpose&lt;/th>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;/thead>
 &lt;tbody>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">command 2&amp;gt;filename&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Redirect stderr to filename&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">command &amp;gt;output 2&amp;gt;filename&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Redirect stderr to file named filename and stdout to file named output&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">command &amp;amp;&amp;gt; filename&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Redirect stderr and stdout to filename&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">command 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;-&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Just suppress error messages. No file created. No error message displayed on screen&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">command 2&amp;gt;/dev/null&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Just suppress error messages.&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">command 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: left">Redirect error messages to standard output. Useful in shell script when you need to forcefully display error messages on screen&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;/tbody>
&lt;/table>
